The most effective way for new IT-based companies to target both the Islamic and Chinese markets would be to perform extensive market research to determine the precise requirements and preferences of these target demographics. This may include researching the cultural and religious beliefs of Muslim customers as well as the technical developments and preferences of Chinese consumers. Additionally, it would be essential for the startup to form partnerships with local firms and influencers in order to establish credibility and expand its reach in these regions. Language localization and compliance with local legislation and laws are two factors to consider. 